message.content: Let the two numbers be $x$ and $y$, with $x>y$. We have the equations $x + y = 19$ and $x - y = 5$. Adding the two equations, we have $2x = 24$, so $x = 12$. Substituting this into the first equation gives $12 + y = 19$, so $y = 7$. The product of $x$ and $y$ is thus $xy = \boxed{84}$.
